page.title: 19TYPICAL DAY AT GREATWOOD
page.content: It's Tuesday Morning! Most of us arrive at school about 08:40. Ah there goes the bell. At nine o'clock school starts and we take register. After that Mr. Cross's English group go off to him and the rest of the class 1 stays with Mr. Brown. I look at the clock, and somtimes wisper{"It's time {for assembly",}one of my favourite times is break.{"Come on hurry up and {get your cricket things out"}I say to my firends. Next it's Maths.I think to myself{"I hope it's not hard" }but before you know it it's finished.Dinner time. Then it's reading, and after that it's Art. We got to do some drawing{"GREAT".}Next {is}P.E. we had the apperatus out. It's been a really good day today.
